---
import Default from "../../../../layouts/Default.astro";
import SideBar from "../../../../components/SideBar_Research.astro";
import NavDataProgram from "../../../../components/Nav_DataProgram.astro";
---

<Default title="ITS JPO - ITS Data Program">
  <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="AboutBanner" -->

  <div class="AboutBanner DataAccess_bkgd">
    <div class="AboutBannerTitle">
      <h1>ITS Data Program</h1>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container-fluid h-100 bodyWrap">
    <div class="row h-100">
      <aside class="col-12 col-md-3 p-3 bg-light">
        <SideBar />
      </aside>
      <main class="col-9 MainContent">
        <div class="container-fluid">
          <NavDataProgram />
          <h2 class="sideways blue">ITS CodeHub</h2>

          <div class="row" style="padding-bottom:0px; margin-bottom:20px; border-bottom-style:none; border-block-width:1px; border-color:gainsboro;">
            <div class="col-lg-7">
              <p>
                ITS CodeHub was developed by the ITS Data Program as a resource for the ITS community to discover and use open-source code, software, and more. ITS CodeHub promotes a reuse-first
                mentality and supports the discovery of open-source code by putting it directly into the hands of developers to customize, transform, expand, and improve, thus contributing to the
                advancement of ITS deployments as trends evolve and needs change.
              </p>

              <button class="Pagebtn externalLink_White btnDark top20Margin" onclick="window.open('https://its.dot.gov/code/');">Visit the ITS Code Hub</button>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-5">
              <img class="sideColumnImg" src="/src/assets/images/data_access/ITS CodeHub_Temp.png" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion accordion-flush" id="myAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne" style="border-bottom:1px solid #d4d4d4;">
              <button id="FAQ_Anchor" type="button" class="accordion-button collapsed" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne">
                <img src="/src/assets/images/accelerating/ITS_AcceleratingDeploymentMockup_FAQs.png" alt="FAQs" class="smallDropdownIcon" /><h3>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h3>
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" data-bs-parent="#myAccordion">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h4>How is the U.S. DOT helping to enable researchers to discover open-source code? And what are the benefits of promoting code-reuse?</h4>
                <p class="read-more-wrap">
                  <a href="https://its.dot.gov/code/">ITS CodeHub</a> promotes a reuse-first mentality and aims to support the discovery of open source-code by putting it directly into the hands of developers
                  to customize, transform, expand, and improve, as trends evolve and needs change. This approach has the benefits of lowering costs, increasing interoperability and transparency, and accelerating
                  the path to high-quality software deployment—collectively advancing our nation’s transportation system.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </div>
  <section class="download bg-primary text-center" id="research" style="padding-top: 2em">
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="col-lg-12">
          <h2>Contacts</h2>
          <p style="padding-bottom: 20px">
            Please explore this site for a more detailed description of the program and progress. We will continue to upload relevant program information for public consumption as it becomes
            available. For inquiries regarding the program, please contact the USDOT Point of Contact below.
          </p>
          <p style="padding-top: 20px; border-top-style: solid; border-color: honeydew; border-width: 2px">
            <b>Murat Omay</b>
          </p>
          <p>Program Manager, ITS Data Program</p>
          <p>ITS Joint Program Office</p>
          <p>(202)-366-4374</p>
          <p>
            <a class="email-footer" href="mailto:Murat.Omay@dot.gov">Murat.Omay@dot.gov</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Default>
